Sanitation Students: Â· demonstrate a knowledge of the principles of sanitation used to prevent the transmission of disease-producing microorganisms from one person/object to another.
4.
Human Growth and Development Students: Â· understand the process of human growth and development and its influence on client needs.
This is evident, for example, when students: v develop a plan to open a child care center with special consideration of program goals, child development, sequential learning concepts, and program evaluation v apply the concept of nurturing to human and public services occupations by volunteering to work in a child care facility v participate in the Focus on Children (STAR) event at a local, State, or national FHA/HERO leadership conference.
2.
Communication Students: Â· demonstrate effective communication skills needed to meet the expectations of human and public services consumers.
This is evident, for example, when students: v exhibit an awareness of multicultural needs of customers of elder-care services v demonstrate creativity and initiative to use alternative resources to communicate effectively with social services customers v know and use the correct terminology and procedures necessary for effective inter- and intra-workplace communication (e.g., internal and external food service customers) v use current technology to communicate effectively with coworkers, supervisors, and consumers v use interactive electronic communication to contact a public official regarding a policy issue.
v practice use of standard communication equipment as employed in the law enforcement and security fields (e.g., radio, fax, email).
5.
Interpersonal Dynamics Students: Â· demonstrate how to interact effectively and sensitively with others.
This is evident, for example, when students: v observe and discuss interdependent relationships and cooperative behaviors between employer/employee, employee/ employee, and employer/consumer v demonstrate and provide services to customers, using a variety of approaches that indicate an understanding of human nature v contribute to a positive environment which enables all groups to be productive and fulfilled v solve group problems effectively in work-related situations v participate in the Food Service-STAR event at a local, State, or national FHA/HERO leadership conference v demonstrate diligence, patience, empathy, and tenacity when serving all private security/law enforcement customers.
